                                        According to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/QZH8VYBF"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/><title level="m">Bybliothecae apostolicae Vaticanae codices manu scripti recensiti iussu Pii XI Pontificis maximi. Codices Aethiopici Vaticani et Borgiani, Barberinianus orientalis 2, Rossianus 865&lt;hi rend="italics"&gt;, I:&lt;/hi&gt; Enarratio codicum</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Sylvain</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Grébaut</t:surname></author><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Eugène</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Tisserant</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Città del Vaticano</pubPlace><publisher>In Bybliotheca Vaticana</publisher><date>1935</date><citedRange unit="page">488</citedRange></bibl>, this would indicate that the two halves of the textblock were bound in reverse order from the original plan.
